31:23.229 --> 31:25.187
- Or you can just
talk to me now.

31:27.059 --> 31:28.974
Keep your hands where
I can see 'em son.

31:31.063 --> 31:32.368
You're under arrest.

31:32.542 --> 31:33.935
Armed robbery and
assault, put 'em up.

31:34.109 --> 31:35.458
Back up here real slow.

31:36.851 --> 31:37.547
- I really wish you

31:37.721 --> 31:40.376
hadn't done this.

31:45.686 --> 31:48.341
- You picked the
wrong bar buddy.

31:51.561 --> 31:53.346
- You don't wanna do this.

31:53.520 --> 31:54.260
-  Oh yeah I do.

32:15.368 --> 32:16.195
- Hey!

32:20.764 --> 32:21.809
- Easy now, brother.

32:32.602 --> 32:33.255
- Colt!

32:37.303 --> 32:41.307
- Those were some fancy
moves back there son.

32:41.481 --> 32:42.830
Where'd you learn to do that?

32:44.527 --> 32:46.703
- A Chinese warlord
from the Ming Dynasty.

32:49.358 --> 32:50.098
- That's funny.

32:52.100 --> 32:53.580
I'll tell you what isn't funny.

32:54.842 --> 32:56.409
We had a murder in
my town last night.

32:57.584 --> 32:58.585
You know what I think?

33:00.108 --> 33:01.675
I think you had
sometin' to do with it.

33:03.329 --> 33:04.895
- You're wastin'
your time, sheriff.

33:05.070 --> 33:06.332
-  Dispatch for Hardy.

33:09.074 --> 33:10.510
- Go for Hardy.

33:10.684 --> 33:12.947
-  We got a 10-67
down on Old Fort Road.

33:13.121 --> 33:15.732
Requesting immediate
assistance, please respond.

33:15.906 --> 33:17.517
- What's going on Meg?

33:17.691 --> 33:18.997
-  You know how we've
been having some trouble

33:19.171 --> 33:21.129
with that biker
gang, Black Cross?

33:21.303 --> 33:22.609
- Yeah.

33:22.783 --> 33:23.610
-  I don't think
they're gonna be

33:23.784 --> 33:25.525
much trouble anymore.

33:28.180 --> 33:29.007
- Problem?

33:43.760 --> 33:44.631
- Jesus.

34:01.909 --> 34:03.302
Hey.

34:03.476 --> 34:04.129
Hey.

34:04.303 --> 34:06.000
- Hey.
- Jesus!

34:06.174 --> 34:07.001
Walter.

34:08.307 --> 34:09.917
Do not sneak up on me like that.

34:12.267 --> 34:14.965
- Eh, I never seen
nothin' like this, Ethan.

34:17.664 --> 34:19.448
Poor Joe saw the whole thing.

34:19.622 --> 34:20.406
- Joe?

34:21.798 --> 34:22.669
Joe?

34:24.584 --> 34:25.498
You all right?

34:25.672 --> 34:27.065
Tell me what happened here.

34:27.239 --> 34:28.153
Start from the beginnin'.

34:28.327 --> 34:28.979
- Well I was just comin' from--

34:29.154 --> 34:30.242
- Not you.

34:30.416 --> 34:31.199
Him.

34:33.332 --> 34:34.202
- Sheriff.

34:35.725 --> 34:38.380
Me and the boys, we was
just going out for a ride.

34:38.554 --> 34:41.035
We thought we'd stop for
just a few brain grenades.

34:43.037 --> 34:45.170
Next thing we know,
six men, they just,

34:45.344 --> 34:47.998
they just came up on
us, from nowhere.

34:50.740 --> 34:53.091
Took our clothes,
our guns, our women.

34:55.267 --> 34:58.661
This one dude, he just,
he just punched his hand

34:58.835 --> 35:02.100
right through Judge and
ripped out his heart.

35:03.710 --> 35:07.627
After that, he was all
interested in our bikes.

35:07.801 --> 35:09.933
Wanted to learn how to
ride, insisted on it.

35:11.152 --> 35:12.719
They were just screwing
around with us.

35:15.548 --> 35:19.160
I don't remember
anything after that.

35:19.334 --> 35:21.858
I just remember waking up,

35:22.032 --> 35:23.860
just seeing everybody dead.

35:24.034 --> 35:25.210
- All right.

35:25.384 --> 35:26.559
All right.

35:26.733 --> 35:28.213
We're gonna get you some help.

35:34.262 --> 35:35.785
- Did they say where
they were headin'?

35:37.396 --> 35:38.527
Drop the gun sheriff.

35:38.701 --> 35:39.615
- Not likely.

35:40.834 --> 35:42.618
- Don't make me ask again.

35:50.409 --> 35:51.497
Which way did they go?

35:52.976 --> 35:55.065
- They were lookin'
for a hide out.

35:55.240 --> 35:57.242
I told them about the
old machine factory.

35:58.852 --> 36:00.027
- You know where that is?

36:03.117 --> 36:04.597
Well let's go.

36:04.771 --> 36:06.860
- Oh no, no, no, you're
not goin' anywhere.

36:08.078 --> 36:10.255
- I hate to do this
to you, sheriff.

36:10.429 --> 36:12.300
But you got a whole lot of
trouble coming your way.

36:12.474 --> 36:14.215
- Now see, what do
you mean by that?

36:15.434 --> 36:16.174
You know what's going on here?

36:16.348 --> 36:17.653
You a part of this?

36:17.827 --> 36:19.786
- You seem like a good
man, and a good man will

36:19.960 --> 36:21.614
get that gentleman to a doc.

36:24.269 --> 36:26.140
-  Go on
Lucy, it's all right.

36:27.837 --> 36:29.099
- Don't worry.

36:29.274 --> 36:30.710
I'll see you soon.

36:30.884 --> 36:32.451
- Oh you're damn right you will.

36:36.803 --> 36:38.152
Meg, I need all my
deputies down here.

36:38.326 --> 36:39.893
I needed 'em 15 minutes ago.

36:41.155 --> 36:42.025
-  Copy that sheriff.

36:42.200 --> 36:43.897
- Walter, go get your gun.

36:44.071 --> 36:44.898
- You bet.

36:47.553 --> 36:50.599
- We are goin' huntin'.

37:00.130 --> 37:00.870
- What is it?

37:03.351 --> 37:04.613
- I'm not goin' any
further with you

37:04.787 --> 37:06.136
until I get some answers.

37:06.311 --> 37:07.486
- Now is not the time.

37:07.660 --> 37:09.314
- Come clean or I walk.

37:09.488 --> 37:10.706
- Lucy.

37:10.880 --> 37:12.360
These men are not
like other men.

37:12.534 --> 37:13.840
It's very important
that I reach them

37:14.014 --> 37:16.364
before nightfall or more
people will get killed.

37:17.670 --> 37:19.367
- You're so full of shit.

37:19.541 --> 37:22.065
- I can't explain
everything right now.

37:22.240 --> 37:23.763
But I need you to believe
me when I tell you

37:23.937 --> 37:26.461
that I don't get to that factory
before your sheriff does,

37:26.635 --> 37:28.289
he will die.

37:28.463 --> 37:29.247
Please.

37:34.164 --> 37:35.383
- All right.

37:35.557 --> 37:36.950
Come on.

37:37.124 --> 37:38.865
It's just up the way.

37:43.696 --> 37:44.958
- All right, here's
the schematics.

37:45.132 --> 37:46.133
- Is that upside-down Ethan?

37:46.307 --> 37:47.134
- Shut up Walter.

37:48.918 --> 37:50.180
Now as far as I can tell,
there are five entrances

37:50.355 --> 37:51.660
into this place.

37:51.834 --> 37:53.009
Sacks, Robertson,
you take the eastern

37:53.183 --> 37:54.837
and western entrance.

37:55.011 --> 37:56.970
Dwayne, you and
Martin take the rear.

37:57.144 --> 37:58.537
Walter, you and I are
gonna go in the front door,

37:58.711 --> 38:00.278
that's right.

38:00.452 --> 38:02.367
According to Joe, there
are six men heavily armed.

38:02.541 --> 38:05.152
You encounter one of these
fugitives, you do not engage.

38:05.326 --> 38:06.675
You call for help, are we clear?

38:06.849 --> 38:07.850
-  Yes, sir.

38:08.024 --> 38:09.025
- Saddle up.

38:26.042 --> 38:27.348
- Those are?

38:27.522 --> 38:29.219
- Oh, motorcycles.

38:29.394 --> 38:31.178
Hogs, choppers.

38:31.352 --> 38:33.572
They're like--
- Steel horses.

38:33.746 --> 38:35.574
- Now you're catchin' on.

38:39.752 --> 38:42.232
- You'd better get
back to town now.

38:42.407 --> 38:43.059
- What?

38:43.233 --> 38:44.191
Why?

38:44.365 --> 38:45.235
- I told you.

38:45.410 --> 38:47.194
These are dangerous men.

38:47.368 --> 38:48.282
- Colt, I--

38:48.456 --> 38:50.066
- This is no place for a woman.

38:50.240 --> 38:51.067
Now go home.

38:52.765 --> 38:54.593
- Did you really just say that?

38:55.811 --> 38:56.595
- Well say what?

38:58.074 --> 38:59.946
- You really are like some
kind of an old fossil,

39:00.120 --> 39:00.947
aren't you?

39:02.165 --> 39:03.036
You know what, fine, whatever.

39:03.210 --> 39:04.429
Do it yourself, I'm gone.

39:09.608 --> 39:11.436
No place for a woman?

39:11.610 --> 39:12.437
Really?

39:21.489 --> 39:23.143
- Damn that woman's
a firecracker.

39:36.765 --> 39:37.810
- Hey Ethan.
- What?

39:38.985 --> 39:41.466
- You, you aint gonna
like, let me killed

39:41.640 --> 39:42.510
or nothin', are ya?

39:44.425 --> 39:46.949
- Walter, you are startin' to
make me regret deputizing you.

39:47.123 --> 39:48.734
Look, just keep your gun up.

39:50.388 --> 39:51.998
Keep your ass clenched.

39:52.172 --> 39:55.001
Do not shoot the wrong person.

39:55.175 --> 39:56.568
- Okay.

40:16.849 --> 40:18.241
Hey.
- What?

40:18.416 --> 40:19.373
- You hear anything?

40:19.547 --> 40:21.288
- I hear you talkin', shut up.

40:24.030 --> 40:25.074
Sacks is down, repeat,

40:25.248 --> 40:28.948
Sacks is down!

40:45.617 --> 40:47.793
- Come on, go, go, go, go.

40:47.967 --> 40:49.142
- Calm down, hold.

40:49.316 --> 40:50.622
Yeah, hold on,
are you all right?

40:50.796 --> 40:52.101
What's going on?
- They're chasing us.

40:52.275 --> 40:54.408
- Okay, all right.

41:42.848 --> 41:43.588
- Dammit.

41:56.296 --> 41:57.471
Got something.

42:00.039 --> 42:01.170
Shh.

42:01.344 --> 42:04.304
Over there, over there.

42:04.478 --> 42:05.348
-  What is it?

42:05.523 --> 42:07.829
- Well hell, I don't know.

42:13.487 --> 42:15.620
- I'm sure he's fine,
let's keep movin'.

42:15.794 --> 42:17.839
- You've gotta be kidding me.

42:18.013 --> 42:20.320
- What, you got an
issue with that, rookie?

42:20.494 --> 42:22.452
- Hold your horses Chuck Norris.

42:22.627 --> 42:24.672
We gotta go find the sheriff.

42:24.846 --> 42:26.631
- Hold on, hold on.

42:26.805 --> 42:28.415
Do you hear that?

42:28.589 --> 42:32.114
- No I didn't hear anyt--

42:32.288 --> 42:34.029
Okay, I heard that.

42:39.644 --> 42:40.296
- What the?

42:40.470 --> 42:41.297
- Oh my...

42:53.005 --> 42:54.572
- This is Hardy, I
hear gunfire, over.

42:54.746 --> 42:56.486
Yeah, we got him.

42:56.661 --> 42:59.881
And man, you are not
gonna believe this shit.

43:22.208 --> 43:23.775
- All right, Mr. Colt.

43:25.298 --> 43:27.343
I need you to shed some
light on what the hell is

43:27.517 --> 43:29.345
going on in my town.

43:30.259 --> 43:31.521
You can start with these.

43:32.566 --> 43:34.089
They all washed up this mornin'.

43:35.308 --> 43:36.918
- Built these with
my bare hands.

43:38.137 --> 43:39.878
- Son, the structure
of these coffins date

43:40.052 --> 43:41.967
back to the mid-1800s.

43:43.098 --> 43:44.230
- The year was 1861.

43:45.753 --> 43:46.885
Civil War just broke.

43:48.234 --> 43:51.237
I joined the Union
Army, 21st infantry,

43:51.411 --> 43:53.282
under the command of my father,

43:53.456 --> 43:55.415
Colonel James Franklin Colt, Sr.

43:55.589 --> 43:58.200
All I ever wanted to
do was make him proud.

43:59.462 --> 44:01.116
- All boys wanna be
like their father.

44:02.335 --> 44:03.597
But this is war, Colt.

44:06.731 --> 44:07.993
- I won't be away forever.

44:11.605 --> 44:13.868
- What if I never see you again?

44:15.087 --> 44:17.742
- Well you can't
think like that.

44:19.918 --> 44:20.701
Here.

44:21.659 --> 44:22.747
I got somethin' for ya.

44:24.487 --> 44:25.750
To help pass the time.

44:26.838 --> 44:28.013
- Wha, what?

44:28.187 --> 44:29.405
What?

44:29.579 --> 44:31.973
- Lydia, I want
you to be my wife.

44:34.454 --> 44:35.150
- What?

44:35.324 --> 44:36.151
- Right now.

44:36.325 --> 44:39.198
Come on.

44:39.372 --> 44:41.200
It was during the
Battle of Bull Run.

44:42.592 --> 44:43.376
That's when they came.

44:43.550 --> 44:45.117
- That's when who came?

44:46.031 --> 44:48.033
- The lycanthrope.

44:48.207 --> 44:49.034
The howlers.

44:50.513 --> 44:53.038
Well they looked human at
first, disguised as soldiers.

44:54.300 --> 44:56.128
The leader of the pack
was a man by the name

44:56.302 --> 44:57.390
of William Price.

44:58.826 --> 45:00.523
They were able to
transform into these

45:00.698 --> 45:02.177
beastly creatures.

45:03.396 --> 45:05.180
Werewolves, as some
would call them.

45:06.921 --> 45:10.925
They took my father's life,
along with most of our garrison.

45:11.099 --> 45:13.928
I was able to escape,
and return home.

45:15.408 --> 45:17.627
It'd been two years
since I'd seen my wife.

45:19.673 --> 45:21.936
One night I went to
town for supplies.

45:22.110 --> 45:24.417
Someone from Price's
gang must've spotted me

45:25.635 --> 45:27.681
'cause when I returned
home, he and his men

45:27.855 --> 45:28.813
were waitin' for me.

45:31.163 --> 45:33.556
I'm sure you all can imagine
how it escalated from there.

45:51.705 --> 45:52.532
- Hello?

45:53.576 --> 45:55.361
Who's out there?

46:04.674 --> 46:05.719
- Lydia?

46:05.893 --> 46:07.373
- Colt.

46:09.592 --> 46:11.203
- No, no, no, no.

46:14.772 --> 46:16.338
- To pass the time.

46:18.340 --> 46:19.124
- No.

46:20.038 --> 46:20.865
No, no, no.

46:29.569 --> 46:34.226
I held my Lydia in my arms,
and then began a storm.

46:35.444 --> 46:37.664
It was unlike any storm
I'd ever seen before.

46:37.838 --> 46:40.536
Lightening was almost blinding.

46:40.710 --> 46:42.712
- We had one hell of
a storm last night.

46:42.887 --> 46:43.975
- Well damn doc.

46:44.149 --> 46:45.759
Let the man finish his story.

46:47.413 --> 46:50.459
- After the sky cleared,
a hooded man came to me

46:50.633 --> 46:51.547
from out of nowhere.

46:52.548 --> 46:53.985
He called himself the Keeper.

46:55.551 --> 46:57.640
Told me that he came
from another dimension,

46:57.815 --> 46:59.947
a place known as the Afterworld.

47:00.121 --> 47:01.731
That he lived many
lifetimes dating back

47:01.906 --> 47:03.124
to the Ming Dynasty.

47:04.343 --> 47:06.301
That he was a warrior
who had slain both man

47:06.475 --> 47:07.259
and beast alike.

47:09.565 --> 47:11.306
I know this all
sounds crazy, but...

47:14.788 --> 47:15.789
The Keeper taught me
all I needed to know

47:15.963 --> 47:16.964
about the Howlers.

47:18.444 --> 47:20.011
Where they lived, what
they ate, and most of all,

47:20.185 --> 47:21.012
how to kill 'em.

47:22.274 --> 47:24.189
The Keeper chose me
to be his hunter.

47:24.363 --> 47:26.321
-  Why do you
think he chose you?

47:26.495 --> 47:28.019
- Because I was driven by rage

47:28.193 --> 47:29.890
that no man was
ever meant to have.

47:31.805 --> 47:33.589
I slaughtered over
a hundred howlers.

47:34.939 --> 47:36.897
It became my obsession.

47:37.071 --> 47:38.203
I finally caught up
to Price and his gang

47:38.377 --> 47:39.857
a couple years after.

47:41.815 --> 47:43.643
Right here, in this very town.

47:45.340 --> 47:48.735
I put an end to the reign of
the demon wolf that night,

47:48.909 --> 47:51.303
or at least I thought I had.

47:52.695 --> 47:56.264
Buried them inside these
coffins along with the scepter.

47:56.438 --> 47:57.570
- The scepter?

47:59.528 --> 48:01.704
- The scepter was given
to me by the Keeper.

48:02.923 --> 48:04.533
It's a weapon, with
mystical powers.

48:04.707 --> 48:06.796
It's even known for
resurrecting the dead.

48:09.277 --> 48:11.062
Somehow it brought
us all back here.

48:12.498 --> 48:15.501
Maybe by some sort of global
shifting in the earth.

48:16.676 --> 48:18.504
That could explain
your big storm.

48:18.678 --> 48:21.986
All I know is, I need
to find this object

48:22.160 --> 48:23.683
because it is the only
weapon that will stop

48:23.857 --> 48:25.293
the last breathing howlers.

48:28.296 --> 48:29.689
Still don't believe me.

48:29.863 --> 48:31.343
- Yeah well if you're
asking if I believe

48:31.517 --> 48:34.520
you're a 150 year old
gunslinger and werewolf hunter,

48:35.913 --> 48:36.870
no, I don't.

48:38.785 --> 48:40.091
Where were you all the time
you were supposed to be dead?

48:40.265 --> 48:41.005
Were you in heaven?

48:41.179 --> 48:42.093
Hell?

48:42.267 --> 48:44.008
Do I look like an idiot to you?

48:45.705 --> 48:47.228
I'll tell you what I do
think, I think these are

48:47.402 --> 48:49.056
a bunch of outlaw cop
killers on the run.

48:49.230 --> 48:50.362
I think you're playin' us.

48:50.536 --> 48:51.537
That's what I think.

48:52.668 --> 48:54.105
Lock him up.

48:54.279 --> 48:56.107
I got bodies pilin' up on ice.

48:56.281 --> 48:58.370
I don't have time
for this voodoo crap.

48:58.544 --> 49:00.633
- But sheriff, we saw them.
- Ethan, just listen--

49:00.807 --> 49:02.940
- Lock him up and
take his weapons.

49:03.114 --> 49:04.898
- That's a very
bad idea, sheriff.

49:05.899 --> 49:07.422
It's a full moon tonight.

49:07.596 --> 49:09.250
Howlers will feast.

49:09.424 --> 49:12.427
- Well, hell, I guess
us ignorant folks

49:12.601 --> 49:14.821
at Temple Wells just
have to lock our doors,

49:14.995 --> 49:15.822
aint that right?

49:17.737 --> 49:18.694
Get him out of here.

49:20.218 --> 49:21.001
- Yes, sir.

49:22.089 --> 49:23.134
- Walter?

49:23.308 --> 49:24.396
You take Lucy home.

49:25.919 --> 49:28.313
I've heard enough of this
nonsense for one night.

49:29.923 --> 49:31.359
- Where you goin', Ethan?

49:34.928 --> 49:37.365
- Well I'm gonna
put out an APB, doc.

49:39.106 --> 49:40.760
On werewolves, apparently.

49:47.071 --> 49:49.682
- He's havin', uh,
woman troubles.

49:52.902 --> 49:54.774
- Come on, you wanna
get some coffee goin'?

49:54.948 --> 49:56.167
Looks like we're gonna
be in for one heck

49:56.341 --> 49:57.298
of a long night.

49:58.604 --> 49:59.431
Right this way.

50:06.133 --> 50:07.787
Yeah, it used to
be a bank vault.

50:10.268 --> 50:12.226
Hey uh, listen.

50:14.576 --> 50:16.143
My partner and I really
appreciate what you

50:16.317 --> 50:19.973
did for us back there and, well,
I just wanna let you know

50:20.147 --> 50:21.018
if there's anything we can
do while you're in here,

50:21.192 --> 50:22.802
then just let me know, okay?

50:25.544 --> 50:26.327
-  Deputy?

50:28.286 --> 50:30.679
- No, Lucy cannot be here.

50:30.853 --> 50:32.725
The sheriff told you
to take her home, Walt.

50:32.899 --> 50:35.510
- Well I tried, but, well
she just wouldn't have it.

50:35.684 --> 50:37.773
- I've spent enough nights
alone out in the middle

50:37.947 --> 50:39.297
of nowhere, and I
don't intend to do it

50:39.471 --> 50:40.994
with monsters runnin' around.

50:41.951 --> 50:43.257
- For crying out loud, Walt.

50:57.967 --> 50:58.751
- Ethan?

50:59.795 --> 51:00.622
- Hi, dad.

51:03.625 --> 51:05.149
- Hey sweetheart, I'm sorry.

51:07.151 --> 51:09.066
It's wonderful to have you home.

51:09.240 --> 51:10.676
- You look stressed.

51:12.417 --> 51:14.984
- I'm sure I do, it's
been a hell of a day.

51:15.159 --> 51:16.682
- What's going on?

51:16.856 --> 51:18.162
- A little trouble downtown.

51:18.336 --> 51:21.034
Sacks and Robertson are dead.

51:21.208 --> 51:23.080
- Oh my god, Ethan,
what happened?

51:24.168 --> 51:25.560
- We're after some fugitives,

51:27.040 --> 51:29.695
and I found Burt Thompson dead
by the river this morning.

51:30.957 --> 51:31.784
- And you're just
now telling me this?

51:31.958 --> 51:33.699
Why didn't you call me?

51:33.873 --> 51:35.179
- Sweetheart, why don't you
go upstairs and freshen up?

51:35.353 --> 51:36.963
I'll take you out for a beer.

51:40.053 --> 51:40.706
Go on.

51:40.880 --> 51:42.186
- Dad.

51:42.360 --> 51:43.883
Are you like in
shock or something?

51:44.057 --> 51:47.016
You never let me drink
alcohol in front of you.

51:47.191 --> 51:48.409
- Yeah well a lot of
things are gonna change

51:48.583 --> 51:49.367
in this family.

51:54.720 --> 51:56.591
A lot of things already
have, isn't that right, babe?

51:56.765 --> 51:58.115
- What are you talkin' about?

52:02.293 --> 52:03.685
- I'm gonna take a shower.

52:06.732 --> 52:08.690
- No, I'm not gonna do that.

52:08.864 --> 52:13.086
Look Lucy, let me make myself
crystal clear with you.

52:13.260 --> 52:16.394
I saw whatever that
thing was at the mill

52:16.568 --> 52:19.658
return to human form
after it went down.

52:19.832 --> 52:21.660
Now, until the committee
decides on what

52:21.834 --> 52:23.357
we're gonna do about
this situation,

52:23.531 --> 52:24.837
I'm gonna do as I'm told.

52:25.011 --> 52:26.926
- The situation?

52:27.100 --> 52:29.581
Would you get your
head out of your ass?

52:29.755 --> 52:32.975
Nine people are dead, two
of them are your friends.

52:33.150 --> 52:34.238
- That's enough!

52:34.412 --> 52:35.369
Both of ya.

52:35.543 --> 52:37.502
You're acting like children.

52:37.676 --> 52:38.851
- All right guys, I
think it's time for us

52:39.025 --> 52:40.069
to get out of here.

52:40.244 --> 52:41.593
- Yeah, that's a great idea.

52:45.118 --> 52:46.511
And Walter, I think you
should go home as well.

52:46.685 --> 52:49.296
- Well if it's all the
same, I just as soon

52:49.470 --> 52:51.255
stay here for a while.

52:51.429 --> 52:53.170
- Walter, not you too.

52:55.607 --> 52:56.956
All right then.

52:57.130 --> 52:58.436
All right look, I
gotta go take a leak.

52:58.610 --> 53:00.177
Keep on eye on him, all right?
- Okay.

53:02.657 --> 53:03.919
- You're startin' to
believe that what I'm

53:04.093 --> 53:05.573
telling you is true,
aren't you Walter?

53:07.096 --> 53:07.967
- Maybe.

53:09.316 --> 53:13.102
Let's uh, let's say
there are werewolves.

53:14.060 --> 53:15.670
You know how to stop 'em right?

53:15.844 --> 53:17.324
- For now.

53:17.498 --> 53:19.283
- Well what's that
supposed to mean, son?

53:19.457 --> 53:20.458
- It's a new time.

53:21.720 --> 53:23.678
They'll evolve,
they'll multiply,

53:23.852 --> 53:25.637
they'll cast their
curse upon others.

53:26.986 --> 53:28.988
It's gonna be harder
and harder to stop 'em

53:29.162 --> 53:31.469
until one day, sooner
rather than later,

53:32.687 --> 53:34.254
the world'll be
covered in darkness.

53:41.000 --> 53:42.306
- You're just joshin' me.

53:44.525 --> 53:45.439
Aren't ya?

53:53.795 --> 53:54.970
- Get me out of here!

53:55.144 --> 53:56.581
- God.

54:03.152 --> 54:06.243
- Your God cannot save you now.

54:06.417 --> 54:08.549
Look at what he did to me.

54:09.507 --> 54:10.899
- Dammit.

54:14.251 --> 54:16.557
- Hey, wolf man!

54:24.522 --> 54:25.914
- You bitch.

54:30.267 --> 54:31.616
- Lucy.

54:31.790 --> 54:32.747
Get the key.

54:39.885 --> 54:41.103
Hey!

54:46.805 --> 54:47.719
- Are you okay?

54:47.893 --> 54:48.894
Are you okay?

55:08.653 --> 55:10.132
- Why is he out of his cell?

55:12.961 --> 55:13.788
Dammit.

55:23.755 --> 55:25.017
Terry, are you all right?

55:26.410 --> 55:27.236
- I'm fine.

55:28.673 --> 55:29.630
It's just a scratch.

55:29.804 --> 55:30.805
He didn't bite me.

55:31.806 --> 55:32.851
- You sure about that?

55:34.374 --> 55:35.767
- I'm sure.

55:35.941 --> 55:37.203
- I think it's safe
to say desperate times

55:37.377 --> 55:39.379
call for desperate measures.

55:39.553 --> 55:40.815
We've been friends a
long time and you're the

55:40.989 --> 55:43.035
sheriff of this town,
so whatever you decide,

55:43.209 --> 55:45.080
I will support you.
- All right, doc.

55:46.647 --> 55:48.257
How do we stop these things?

55:48.432 --> 55:50.434
- To stop 'em, you
need to understand 'em.

55:50.608 --> 55:53.306
- All right, make me understand.

55:53.480 --> 55:55.656
- Ancient legends say
the werewolf will only

55:55.830 --> 55:57.441
prowl at night
under a full moon.

55:58.616 --> 55:59.312
Is that true?

55:59.486 --> 56:00.313
- Are you done?

56:01.270 --> 56:02.097
- What?

56:03.229 --> 56:04.709
I grew up on monster movies.

56:05.797 --> 56:07.189
- Go ahead.

56:07.364 --> 56:09.366
- A full moon gives
'em miraculous powers.

56:09.540 --> 56:12.717
But a howler can attack at
any time during the day.

56:12.891 --> 56:14.196
Price knows I'm here.

56:14.371 --> 56:15.459
He's gonna come for me.

56:18.113 --> 56:21.682
We need weapons, and
a place to dig in.

56:21.856 --> 56:24.119
Somewhere where we
can see what's comin'.

56:24.293 --> 56:25.164
- I know a place.

56:27.558 --> 56:29.734
- You mean that house
you just remodeled?

56:29.908 --> 56:32.650
Oh yeah, Karen's gonna be
completely okay with that.

56:32.824 --> 56:35.653
- No, no, I'm not
talking about my house.

56:35.827 --> 56:37.350
I'm talking about the mayor's.

56:38.612 --> 56:39.396
Anything else?

56:40.788 --> 56:42.181
- Yes.

56:42.355 --> 56:43.965
I need to learn how
to ride a truck.

56:45.010 --> 56:45.837
- Drive a truck.

56:47.186 --> 56:48.796
You wanna learn
to drive a truck.

56:50.581 --> 56:51.669
- Oh god, help us.

57:07.859 --> 57:08.642
- Ethan?

57:11.602 --> 57:12.385
Ethan.
- What?

57:12.559 --> 57:13.821
- What are you doing?

57:13.995 --> 57:16.128
- Get Emily, get
dressed, we're leavin'.

57:16.302 --> 57:17.216
- She's asleep.

57:17.390 --> 57:18.652
- Well wake her up, Karen.

57:20.828 --> 57:22.787
- Ethan, just tell
me what's going on.

57:22.961 --> 57:23.744
- Dammit!

57:33.275 --> 57:35.408
How long, Karen?

57:36.322 --> 57:37.932
It's killing me inside.

57:38.106 --> 57:40.631
Of all the people you
could've picked, Bob Barlow?

57:42.067 --> 57:45.244
You know what that son
of bitch did to me?

57:47.115 --> 57:49.378
- A year, almost.

57:52.207 --> 57:53.078
- Jesus.

57:57.952 --> 58:00.389
- You and I, we were
fighting a lot and

58:01.956 --> 58:05.351
we were both just
working all the time.

58:05.525 --> 58:09.616
And Emily, she was, she
was off just fighting

58:09.790 --> 58:11.226
her own life and...

58:16.928 --> 58:18.103
Ethan, I never meant--
- No.

58:18.277 --> 58:19.496
You don't get to say that.

58:24.326 --> 58:25.850
I don't know why
people say that,

58:26.024 --> 58:27.460
"I never meant to hurt you."

58:28.635 --> 58:29.331
You've been banging
the mayor of the town

58:29.506 --> 58:30.376
like a screen door.

58:33.379 --> 58:35.555
How do you think that's
gonna make me feel?

58:35.729 --> 58:36.948
- Is that true?

58:40.473 --> 58:43.911
- You weren't supposed
to hear that, baby.

58:48.612 --> 58:49.526
- Mom.

58:51.571 --> 58:53.138
So that explains a thing or two.

58:55.706 --> 58:57.272
- I'm sorry Em. I really
messed things up.

58:57.446 --> 58:58.535
- Yeah, you sure did.

59:06.194 --> 59:09.807
- Now this, is a
good lookin' truck.

59:09.981 --> 59:11.635
- This is a car.

59:11.809 --> 59:14.551
It belonged to Deputy Grant
and if you can drive this,

59:14.725 --> 59:16.378
you can drive just
about anything.

59:17.466 --> 59:18.511
Let's give it a try.

59:28.695 --> 59:30.741
Brakes, hit the brakes!

59:32.656 --> 59:34.092
This is gonna take some work.

59:38.531 --> 59:41.447
This is a classic, so you
gotta treat it real gentle.

