1:00:01.510 --> 1:00:03.338
Not bad, tiger.

1:00:03.512 --> 1:00:04.731
Not bad at all.

1:00:11.608 --> 1:00:13.479
- Hey sheriff, what's
this curfew all about?

1:00:13.653 --> 1:00:15.524
- Well, you hear what
happened to Burt Thompson?

1:00:15.699 --> 1:00:16.917
- Yeah.

1:00:17.091 --> 1:00:18.223
- That's what the
curfew's about.

1:00:21.313 --> 1:00:22.531
- Well this is it.

1:00:22.706 --> 1:00:23.881
This is all we have.

1:00:25.056 --> 1:00:26.100
- We'll make it work.

1:00:37.329 --> 1:00:38.243
-  Excuse me.

1:00:41.115 --> 1:00:42.247
- God.

1:00:42.421 --> 1:00:43.814
Honey, are you all right?

1:00:43.988 --> 1:00:44.902
- Let me get you somethin'.

1:00:45.076 --> 1:00:46.468
- No, I'm okay.

1:00:49.863 --> 1:00:52.387
It must just be a
stomach bug or something.

1:00:52.561 --> 1:00:53.388
Um...

1:00:55.652 --> 1:00:56.565
Come on, let's get going.

1:00:56.740 --> 1:00:57.871
We've gotta get to the sheriff.

1:01:00.221 --> 1:01:01.048
- What?

1:01:01.222 --> 1:01:02.006
What is it?

1:01:03.398 --> 1:01:04.138
- Nothin'.

1:01:04.312 --> 1:01:05.139
Let's go.

1:01:09.753 --> 1:01:10.579
I'll drive.

1:01:27.814 --> 1:01:29.381
- Ethan, why don't
I just leave town?

1:01:29.555 --> 1:01:31.600
I can take Emily and--
- Emily's with Lucy.

1:01:31.775 --> 1:01:32.601
She's fine.

1:01:33.646 --> 1:01:34.908
I wanna get this over with.

1:01:37.476 --> 1:01:40.697
Wait a minute, just wait.

1:01:44.831 --> 1:01:46.398
I need you to help
me understand.

1:01:48.835 --> 1:01:50.794
I get kicked off the force
in Dallas, you say if

1:01:50.968 --> 1:01:54.275
we move here, that it'll
be a blessing in disguise.

1:01:54.449 --> 1:01:55.799
Remember that?

1:01:55.973 --> 1:01:58.715
You say you want a simple life.

1:01:58.889 --> 1:02:00.194
- I did.

1:02:00.368 --> 1:02:02.327
- You told me you wanted
to grow old together.

1:02:02.501 --> 1:02:03.284
- I did.

1:02:04.546 --> 1:02:06.723
- Okay well then,
I don't understand.

1:02:11.815 --> 1:02:12.641
- I don't know.

1:02:18.082 --> 1:02:19.692
You were never around,
Ethan, you were married

1:02:19.866 --> 1:02:22.347
to your job then
and I was lonely and

1:02:23.522 --> 1:02:24.871
we moved here,
nothing got better.

1:02:31.878 --> 1:02:33.880
We're never gonna get
past this, are we?

1:02:36.317 --> 1:02:37.797
You're never gonna forgive me.

1:02:39.320 --> 1:02:41.453
- It's just with me, there's
some lines you don't cross.

1:02:44.761 --> 1:02:46.937
- If it's any consolation--
- It's not.

1:03:03.910 --> 1:03:05.651
- Mrs. Hardy.

1:03:05.825 --> 1:03:07.958
- You can cut the Miss Hardy
crap, I need to see your boss.

1:03:08.915 --> 1:03:10.787
- Nobody walks past me.

1:03:10.961 --> 1:03:12.223
- Where is he?

1:03:15.530 --> 1:03:16.836
I'll find him.

1:03:17.010 --> 1:03:18.098
- You should've have moved.

1:03:28.674 --> 1:03:31.329
- Is this a bad time, Bob?

1:03:31.503 --> 1:03:32.460
- Well, shit.

1:03:32.634 --> 1:03:34.027
- Yeah.

1:03:34.201 --> 1:03:37.552
- I wish you'd have let
me know you was comin'.

1:03:39.859 --> 1:03:41.295
You all right there, Princess?

1:03:43.123 --> 1:03:44.690
- Remind me again, Bob,
how many years you get

1:03:44.864 --> 1:03:46.431
for illegal gun smuggling?

1:03:46.605 --> 1:03:47.432
It's a bunch, isn't it?

1:03:47.606 --> 1:03:48.999
- Yeah.

1:03:49.173 --> 1:03:49.869
